# self-loop-eval

**Self-Evaluation & Self-Training Loop System** — an RL layer for iterative self-improvement through "aha moments."

## Core Concept

A student model solves real-world coding problems, self-evaluates, submits to a teacher, and when stuck, receives thinking scaffolds (not answers). These thoughts are trained via LoRA to create genuine "aha moments" — the student internalizes better reasoning and demonstrably improves.

## The Aha Moment Cycle

```
1. Student receives a real-world problem
2. Student solves it (initial attempt)
3. Student self-evaluates (critique + score)
4. Student self-corrects → submits ALL work to teacher
5. Teacher evaluates independently
6. If NO improvement from self-correction:
   → Teacher injects a "thought" (thinking scaffold, NOT the answer)
   → Thought becomes LoRA training data
   → Student retries with internalized thinking
   → 💡 AHA MOMENT: "I know what I could have done better!"
7. Complete cycle repeats 10 times for validation
```

## Quick Start

```bash
# Install
pip install -e .

# Install with training dependencies
pip install -e ".[training]"

# Run with dev tools
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run a single training cycle
self-loop-eval run

# Run eval only (no training)
self-loop-eval eval

# View metrics
self-loop-eval metrics
```

## Project Structure

```
self_loop_eval/
├── environments/          # Task domains (coding, etc.)
│   ├── base.py            # Abstract TaskEnvironment
│   ├── coding.py          # Code execution + test case evaluation
│   └── real_world_problems.py  # LRU Cache, Rate Limiter, etc.
├── models/                # LLM wrappers
│   ├── student.py         # Student model (learner)
│   ├── teacher.py         # Teacher model (guide)
│   └── prompts.py         # All prompt templates
├── eval_loop/             # Self-evaluation engine
│   ├── aha_cycle.py       # ⭐ The Aha Moment Cycle Engine
│   ├── loop.py            # Basic self-eval loop
│   ├── convergence.py     # Convergence detection
│   └── round_state.py     # Round/loop state tracking
├── training/              # Training pipeline
│   ├── data_collector.py  # Collects loop results → training tuples
│   ├── sft_formatter.py   # Formats for supervised fine-tuning
│   ├── lora_trainer.py    # LoRA fine-tuning via PEFT
│   └── scheduler.py       # Nightly training orchestrator
├── rl/                    # Reinforcement learning layer
│   ├── rewards.py         # Reward functions
│   └── trainer.py         # PPO/DPO training
├── metrics/               # Tracking & evaluation
│   └── tracker.py         # Improvement, teacher dependency, accuracy
├── config.py              # System configuration
└── cli.py                 # Command-line interface
```

## Running Tests

```bash
pytest tests/ -v
```
